results.title: Winter Wonderland Bead Loom Cuff Pattern
results.description:
This happy snowman is cheering over the gorgeous winter weather....day and night time, as the silver lined Delicas continue to fall!
_____________

Iâm offering this bead loom pattern, created with color depth, which will lift your two dimensional beading, off the warps!

Each pattern is created to be woven, with 11/0 Miyuki Delicas. Please consider purchasing the necessary Delica numbers, in one gram packs, as offered by your local bead store, first  :D , or on line. Remember there are 200(+/-)Delicas per gram. The bead list you will receive, with the pattern purchase, offers the Delica count required, per Delica Color number, for each pattern. Use this as your guide to purchase the beads.

Where I am able to offer a picture, of this pattern finished in beads, it is included in the photo album of this page. Not all of my patterns have been completed and shared, for me to offer a finished piece, but I am very confident you will be pleased, with the Delica Bead Color choices, I have made, to create this pattern. Consider using the colors suggested, to recreate the best rendition, of the pattern. Bead finishes, as well as color, is taken into consideration when I create the pattern and is not always relayed in the sample drawing, of the pattern. 

An instruction for sizing each cuff pattern, to fit the various wrist sizes, is already included, in this pattern purchase, and very easy to follow. Clasp selection is left up to the Bead Loom Weaver. Please use your personal creativity to edge the cuffs. We ship this print rolled in a thick mailer tube.
 
 
16x24 â Premium Giclee Print
 
This size print is a crowd favorite!  The size allows you to boast the  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes) in any setting and you gain the value of an ultra high-end giclee at a great price.  Printed on thick (310gsm) textured acid-free watercolor paper. Giclee prints are the standard reproduction medium for museums and premium art galleries worldwide. 
 
Giclee (French for 'to spray') is a printing process where millions of ink droplets are sprayed onto a high-quality paper. This printing process allows for dynamic, almost 3D appearance due to the high color gamut (millions of colors), smooth printing texture, and amazing details in shadows, creating depth.
 
We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum level archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.

results.title: Adirondack chairs at sunset in Biddeford Pool  scenic hi res digital image
results.description:
Raised near here, I love to return to Biddeford Pool whenever I can, especially in summer.  Biddeford Pool is a beach side community in southern Maine. Squeaky powdered sand beaches that go on for miles and a small cove or "Pool" that protects boats and homes in bad weather. These chairs were grouped together, facing the sunset, one June evening. BlueBisbee Native American Jewelry


About Jewelry We Sell

Pueblo Indian custom says turquoise steals its blue color from the sky. Native American tribes such as the Navajo, Zuni, Hopi have used turquoise in their silver jewelry for hundreds of years. Silver Rings, bangles, cuffs, concha belts, bola neckties, squash blossoms, pendants and other tribal Native American jewelry pieces have been adorned with blue turquoise, green turquoise, and together with lapis, mother of pearl, jet, onyx and coral in fine inlay work. 
In the early days, Turquoise was abundant and the finest specimens were used in the older items of Indian Tribal turquoise jewelry. Today, most of the mines in the American Southwest are depleted and today's Navajo, Zuni and Hopi artists use turquoise from China and Persia. One way collectors are able to find some of the old turquoise favorites such as Sleeping Beauty Turquoise, Bisbee Turquoise, Spiderweb Turquoise, Lander Blue Turquoise, Lone Mountain Turquoise, Number 8 Turquoise, Kingman, Fox, Cripple Creek is by finding an Old Pawn or Vintage Native American jewelry piece with an old gemstone.

ABOUT OUR STAMPS
Pink Pueblo custom stamps are high quality wood mounted photopolymer stamps. Our hand made stamps are permanently mounted on maple wood mounts. Please note each stamp is a custom creation and may vary slightly in size or text layout (due to length or size of text).

ABOUT OUR INK
We are proud to offer ColorBoxÂ® Premium Dye Ink by ClearSnapÂ®. Inkpads are not automatically included with your stamp purchase; if you want to include an inkpad please select your color above. ColorBoxÂ® Premium Dye Ink is fast-drying ink that is washable with water, and dries well on glossy or coated papers. Inkpad dimensions: L 4" x W 2.5" x D .5".

HOW TO ORDER
Please enter the text to be included on the stamp in the Message to Seller exactly as you want the text to appear on the completed stamp. Unless previously discussed, your stamp will ship 3-5 business days after proof approval via United States Post Office Priority Mail. You will receive a shipping notification as soon as your package is on it's way! If you need faster shipping, please contact me. Please note stamps orders will not be cancelled or refunded after proof approval.

CARING FOR YOUR STAMP
Stored and cared for properly, your stamp will last for years. Photopolymer is prone to staining, so gently wipe your stamp with a damp cloth after use. Don't ever submerge your stamp in water, and ensure your stamp is thoroughly dry after cleaning. Store your stamp indoors and away from direct sunlight to prevent yellowing. If your stamp does stain, don't panic - this won't affect it's performance! Don't use solvent or oil-based inks, and never use harsh cleaning chemicals on your stamp.

COMMERCIAL USE
Pink Pueblo stamps may be used to decorate products or packaging for your business. However, our artwork may not be used as your logo or duplicated.

results.title: Nature Jewelry Real Butterfly Wing ring Bracelet Eco friendly Jewelry Earthy Butterfly Cuff Insect Taxidermy Gold Bangle Asian Japanese
results.description:
This fascinating bracelet has been handcrafted from the gorgeous and intricate wings of a real Papilio Xuthus Butterfly, also known as the Asian Swallowtail. The wings are embedded under an 18x25mm magnified glass cabochon and set in your choice of  antique gold (as pictured), shiny gold, antique silver, or gunmetal. 

The Asian Swallowtail Butterfly (Papilio Xuthus) is commonly found in Japan & Southern China. Its wings are very detailed with a delicate black pattern on a pale yellow background with blue and orange spots. Each piece will come with an organza gift bag and literature on the species of butterfly!

This listing is for one bracelet.

*NOTE* No Butterflies are harmed in the making of my jewelry! All butterflies are raised on butterfly farms and sanctuaries and allowed to live their full lifespan, which averages about 1 month, and then collected and sold so that their beauty can live on! Butterfly Farming actually helps to preserve rain forests and also assures the survival of natural butterfly habitats. Native people are encouraged to grow plants and raise insects opposed to clearing land for cash crops. A portion of my profits are donated to the Rainforest Alliance, a nonprofit organization dedicated to preserving the Rainforest and the many species that live within it, including the Blue Morpho Butterfly!

results.description:
These adorable teardrop necklaces are made with real butterfly wings! This listing is for one REAL butterfly wing necklace of your choice (read below on how I ethically obtain the butterfly wings!) Each butterfly wing is embedded under a large 3/4" x 1.25" magnified glass teardrop and set in your choice of an antique gold (as pictured), antique silver, or black gunmetal setting! Each necklace will arrive in its own organza gift bag with literature on the species of butterfly! These are an Original Chrysalis Studios design Â© 2015.

Choose which type of butterfly wing you would like in your necklace below!

Butterfly wing species / color options going from left to right in first photo:

1. Monarch ""Danaus Plexippus" Butterfly from North America (Orange & Black)

2. Blue Morpho "Morpho Rhetenor" Butterfly from Brazil (Iridescent Royal Blue)

3. Sunset Moth "Urania Ripheus" Moth from Madagascar (Iridescent Pink & Teal)

The Chain measures approximately 18 inches and is meant to rest on the upper chest (as pictured). If you would prefer your pendant on a long 28 inch chain that hangs down low, just message me and I can switch it out. (Or if you would prefer to measure yourself and let me know exactly how long you would like your chain, I will be happy to make a custom length chain just for you.)

*NOTE* No Butterflies are harmed in the making of my jewelry! All butterflies are raised on butterfly farms and sanctuaries and allowed to live their full lifespan, which averages about 1 month, and then collected and sold so that their beauty can live on! Butterfly Farming actually helps to preserve rain forests and also assures the survival of natural butterfly habitats. Native people are encouraged to grow plants and raise insects opposed to clearing land for cash crops. A portion of my profits are donated to the Rainforest Alliance, a nonprofit organization dedicated to preserving the Rainforest and the many species that live within it, including the Blue Morpho Butterfly!

results.title: Hair Extension Hook Beads and Pliers Tool Kit
results.description:
LISTING INCLUDES: 

1 pair of pliers for installing and taking off links...
1 wood hair extension hook tool...
15 piece starter kit micro links...


                  Installing the Extension

1. First you will need to take one of the micro links and place it onto the hair hook.  Then using the hair hook select a small section of hair (best if under a layer of hair or behind the ear to hide the link) and hook the hair hook onto the hair. 

2.  Next slide the micro link over the end of the hook, and around the hair at the root.  Once you have your micro link around a piece of hair simply slide the tip of the Featherhead into the link. 

3.  Using the hair extension clamp apply gentle pressure onto the micro link to hold the extension in place.  It is important to make sure the adhesive tip is under the link when you clamp it down. This ensures that the extension will remain in place, and single feathers wonât fall out. Once the link is clamped down firmly, trim the tip of the feather hair extension with a scissors if necessary.

results.title: Precision-Cut Lavender Luc Yen Spinel
results.description:
Here is a 1.04 carat lavender pink spinel from Luc Yen, Vientnam. Not many Luc Yen spinels on the market these days, so this is a rare find. It measures 7 x 5.8 mm. It is VS1 clarity (any spots you can see in the last two photos is from the stone sticking to my finger). It is precision cut, which gives it nice luster and diamond-like sparkle. The color is a very pretty medium-light lavender pink (and a bit more satulated than my pictures were able to capture). Spinel is completely natural and untreated. 

Spinels are not widely known in the jewelry market because good spinels are fairly rare. However, they make excellent choices for engagement rings because they are very durable and suitable for daily wear, they have high refractive index and are more sparkly than sapphires, they are untreated in any way, and they are priced much better than comparable sapphires (although their prices are going up very quickly lately). Very few spinels are coming out of Vietnam, and they are well known for their crisp cryltal and beautiful colors (without any undesirable gray). 
This spinel would make an excellent stone for an engagement ring with a diamond halo or a rose gold milgrain bezel stacking ring (as we have in other listings).

Benefits of buying a special gem from us:
-We are happy to provide additional photos or videos, to help you make a decision
-We offer a 5-day inspection period. If you are not satisfied for any reason, you can return the gem in its original undamaged condition for a full refund (buyer pays return shipping).
-We will be happy to design a special jewelry piece for you using this gem. You can return the gem to us at any time and we will give you credit of 20% of the gem's price towards the cost of the mount.
-If you don't see what you are looking for in the listings, please contact us and we will be happy to source your special gem for you.
-We can get a report from AGL or GIA on your request. All the costs of obtaining the report are buyer's responsibility.

Thank you.

*** new batch , new picture , please be advise 

More about Pietersite
Pietersite was discovered by Sid Pieters in 1962 while he was prospecting some farmland in Namibia, Africa. After his discovery, he registered the find in the mineral records of Britain. His discovery was published in 1964, and the material was named pietersite. Currently there are only two known sources of pietersit: African and Chinese. Pietersite is considered a type of tiger's eye, having the same properties as tiger's eye but with different patterns due to its brecciated formation.

The fibrous structure in pietersite has been folded, stressed, even fractured and/or broken apart via the Earth's geologic processes. The fibrous materials have then been reformed and naturally recemented together by quartz. Stones and crystals that go through this process are referred to as brecciated, creating a finished product with multiple colors, hues and superb chatoyancy. While pietersite has the lovely chatoyancy of tiger eye, it is not found in continuously structured bands. Rather it can form in swirls, swathes and fibrous (sometimes linear) segments. Thus the structure of the fibrous streaks in pietersite may appear rather chaotic, and can flow or exist in many directions side-by-side like bold paint strokes.

African pietersite is the most sought after pietersite due to its wide rage of colors. Colors include various blues, golds and reds, that may appear together or alone. Blue is the rarest color, followed by red. The blues range from a baby blue to dark midnight hue. Golds can be light to very deep and rich, sometimes having a reddish hue. All fibrous color variations will have a superb and striking chatoyancy, the bright and subtly changing shimmer of color that moves along the surface of a gemstone as it is viewed from varying angles.

Chinese pietersite is said to have been discovered in 1993, but did not come to market until 1997. Chinese pietersite exhibits a slightly different variations in color and patterns from the pietersite found in Africa. Its colors are primarily golden and bronze, as seen in the pictures to the right, but can also be found in blue shades.

***** NOTE: This listing is for one bag *****

Ready for a BOARing history lesson?

Bayonets have been around for a long, long time. But did you know its origins had little to do with warfare? Bayonets were actually invented out of necessity by some of the earliest wild boar hunters. See, boars are infamous for their razor sharp tusks and a willingness to defend themselves, even to the death. If a hunter was to miss his shot or only wounded the boar, a death-charge was always imminent.

With an instinct to always run towards the gunshots, wild boars are characteristically covered in scars; which is why we love it when we can get our hands on some authentic hides. No two sections of boar hide will ever look the same. If you have been eyeing our Shave Bag, DOPP/Toiletry Bag, or Mini Bag but still need just a bit more enticement; I think you found it.

results.description:
*  *  *  WHO WE ARE *  *  *
 
We are a dynamic art company that specializes in the world's leading imagery. Our collection includes original works created by our in-house art team, modern photography, home & office decor trends, antique maps, vintage posters, and everything in between. With an ever growing collection of world-renowned imagery, Lantern Press is a trendsetter known to decorate homes and major resorts - as well as the sets of commercials, films, and television shows.
 
If you're seeking the perfect art to frame for your home or office, we're certain we have a piece you will connect with. Peruse our collection here, featuring thousands of available images in multiple sizes and mediums. We'd also like to take this time to thank you if you've purchased from us before, or plan to today. You are supporting artists who care deeply about their art form, and a company that is proud to print these amazing images in America. Your support allows us to continue doing what we love - creating beautiful art.
 
 
*  *  *  SIZE OPTIONS *  *  *
 
9x12 â High Quality Art Print
 
This size print is great for portfolios, collecting, and a nice gift item.  Many of our customers to a tryptic installation (where you frame 3 and install side by side in a hallway, bedroom, or area that can use more  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes)).  If you are looking for more of a statement piece, we highly recommend moving to a larger size that we offer.   Framing is readily available at any framer and many online frame suppliers.  Printed on a heavy stock on our high-end digital printing press. We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum-quality archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.  We ship this print flat, unless purchased along with another print size listed below.
 
 
12x18 â High Quality Art Print
 
This size print is a statement piece and will be large enough to show detail and capture the attention of the viewer.  Framing is readily available at any framer and many online frame suppliers.  Printed on a heavy stock on our high-end digital printing press.  We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum-quality archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.  We ship this print rolled in a thick mailer tube.
 
 
16x24 â Premium Giclee Print
 
This size print is a crowd favorite!  The size allows you to boast the  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes) in any setting and you gain the value of an ultra high-end giclee at a great price.  Printed on thick (310gsm) textured acid-free watercolor paper. Giclee prints are the standard reproduction medium for museums and premium art galleries worldwide. 
 
Giclee (French for 'to spray') is a printing process where millions of ink droplets are sprayed onto a high-quality paper. This printing process allows for dynamic, almost 3D appearance due to the high color gamut (millions of colors), smooth printing texture, and amazing details in shadows, creating depth.
 
We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum level archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.
 
The Giclee will ship rolled in a thick mailer tube, rolled with archival tissue.
 
 
24x36 â Premium Giclee Print
 
Same as the 16x24 giclee print above, but even bigger!  If you are getting someone an important gift, this is the way to go.  Or, if you are wanting this  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes) to be a statement piece in a room, look no further â this is what you want.  This size is a standard framing size, looks amazing in any setting, and still arrives to you in a convenient tube.
 
*  *  *  IMAGE SIZE / PAPER SIZE *  *  *
 
We print whatâs called âto paperâ which means that we print the image as big as we can onto the paper size.  The 9x12 and 12x18 prints get within about 1/8â to the paper edge, which is great for framing.  The 16x24 and 24x36 are printed âfull bleedâ which means we print the image right to the paper edge, so there is no white border (unless itâs an odd proportion â for instance, if the image is square, and you purchase a 24x36 print, you will receive a 24x24 print).

16x24 â Premium Giclee Print
 
This size print is a crowd favorite!  The size allows you to boast the  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes) in any setting and you gain the value of an ultra high-end giclee at a great price.  Printed on thick (310gsm) textured acid-free watercolor paper. Giclee prints are the standard reproduction medium for museums and premium art galleries worldwide. 
 
Giclee (French for 'to spray') is a printing process where millions of ink droplets are sprayed onto a high-quality paper. This printing process allows for dynamic, almost 3D appearance due to the high color gamut (millions of colors), smooth printing texture, and amazing details in shadows, creating depth.
 
We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum level archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.

The 9x12 and 12x18 prints get within about 1/8â to the paper edge, which is great for framing.  The 16x24 and 24x36 are printed âfull bleedâ which means we print the image right to the paper edge, so there is no white border (unless itâs an odd proportion â for instance, if the image is square, and you purchase a 24x36 print, you will receive a 24x24 print).

results.title: All Natural Deodorant Paste - Kaolin Clay - Silky Deodorant Cream - Coconut Oil - Chamomile Flower - Tea Tree & Lemon Oil - Essential Oils
results.description:
I woke up one morning, with a realization that I should stop using chemical-laden commercial antiperspirants. All this talk of aluminum, and other questionable ingredients, has given me the heeby-jeeby's. 

So, after a lot of research, and multiple visits to the drawing board, I've come up with a formulation that I love! It is pleasing in consistency, very effective against odor, and good for the skin. The texture is a firm paste, that spreads easily on your skin, and feels skin silky and soft. It is quickly absorbed, and scented with the camphoraceous lift of Tea Tree and lemon pure essential oils. 

Natural deodorants contain no aluminum. Although the vegetable and clay powders will help to absorb moisture, it will not clog your pores to prevent sweat. Sweat doesn't bother me. I understand that it's a perfect cooling and detoxifying system. That being said, I work closely with people, and prefer to smell nice :)

Extra-virgin, organic coconut oil possesses amazing antibacterial and anti-fungal properties, and is an effective deodorant all on it's own. Chamomile flower soothes, while the essential oils inhibit bacteria growth. 
Zinc oxide is a naturally occurring mineral, used in diaper ointments, soothing skin salves, and natural sun-block. Combining these ingredients creates a deodorant that is more effective, and easier to use than plain coconut oil. A drop of beeswax prevents separation. 

Using fingertips, gently massage a small, pea-sized chunk under each arm. A little goes a long way! I like to wait for it to absorb before I get dressed. 
 
**Of course, body chemistry differs from person to person, but this deodorant works better for me than anything I've ever purchased. I recently received this email regarding it's efficacy:

"I bought this deodorant as an alternative to the chemicals in traditional deodorants. Ingredients:
arrow root powder, baking soda, organic, extra-virgin coconut oil, kaolin clay, cocoa butter, beeswax, organic chamomile flower powder, zinc oxide, tea tree essential oil, lemon essential oil

**A small percentage of the population is sensitive to baking soda. If you start to develop a rash, you may want to discontinue use. Some say your body will acclimate, and the rash is a result of your skin 'detoxifying' from all the aluminum. 
I believe it's probably a combination of things. Baking soda tends to create a more alkaline environment, which is the reason bacteria and fungi will not grow there. This means your skin is going through a slight PH change, which can cause a temporary rash. Irritation can also be caused mechanically, by baking soda's rough edges. To off-set this, I buffer with plenty of other super soft, and soothing powders.
I have been using this formula for months now, and have not experienced any problems with rash. None of my testers (all fully-consenting people, no animals) have reported any such issues. However, it's always best to do your own research, and product testing before use.

results.title: Antique North African Silver Fibula - Morocco
results.description:
This is a beautiful antique silver fibula from Morocco. This was bought in Marrakesh.
The metal is usually some sort of metal alloy, mostly due to the fact that the silversmiths do use whatever raw material they can find: old coins, silverware etc... And here the central part of the fibula is indeed a coin.
This is a very delicate piece that is part of the traditional North African costume for cloak closure purposes. In addition, this particular fibula can be worn as a pendant thanks to the pinnacle-like  detail at the top of the piece that can double up as a bail of sorts.
The fibula measures1.25" by 4.5".

results.description:
Personalized Engraved Cobalt Wedding Ring With 18K Gold Plated Flower Design 


What are the advantages of Cobalt Chrome rings?

Superior Strength:

Our cobalt rings use the same kind of cobalt alloy (cobalt chrome) used to built aircraft jet engines. It is so strong that it would not bend out-of-round and it retains its shape permanently.

Scratch Resistance:

Cobalt chrome is harder than stainless steel, therefore, harder to scratch. Although not 100% scratch proof like tungsten carbide, cobalt chrome is much harder than titanium, and all precious metals including platinum, gold and silver.

Shatter Proof:

Cobalt wedding bands will never shatter or crack. Due to the fact that cobalt alloys are malleable, cobalt rings are shatter proof.

Permanent Premium White Color:

Cobalt rings have color comparable to white gold and platinum jewelry. Moreover, since cobalt rings are not plated with rhodium, which will eventually wear off, they will retain its premium white color forever.

Hypoallergenic:

The same cobalt chrome material used to make surgical tools is used to make cobalt rings. They do not contain any harmful substances that would cause allergic reactions.

results.description:
13in x 19in Giclee print on semi-gloss paper printed on a Pixma Pro-100. Custom sizes available. 

Description: 
This work takes three famous works by Andy Warhol, Gustave Caillebotte, and Claude Monet decomposes the images into pixels, and then takes the average color at each pixel. The resulting image is a strange, beautiful combination of three famous works art. 

Artist statement: 
My work explores the relationship between chance, randomness, probability and the natural human impulse to seek visual structure. With influences as diverse as Piet Mondrian, Vilmos HuszÃ¡r, and Bart van der Leck of the Dutch neoplasticism (Nieuwe Beelding in Dutch) movement of the early 20th century and contemporary artist Damien Hirst, my goal is to explore these connections through digital art, marrying aesthetic principles with data visualizations generated using statistical computing software and pseudo-random number generation.
http://statsinthewild.com/art/statement/

results.title: Glass on Glass Mosaic in Vintage Window - Poppy Splendor Collection - Himalayan Blue

results.title: 2oz Regular CA glue (THIN) instant super glue with pin-cap
results.description:
2 ounce bottle of THIN viscosity CA "Super Glue"

HYPERBOND brand by CA-Plus adhesives - sold by RabidModels.com

What kind of glue do you need?  The thicker the viscosity of the glue, the more slowly it dries and the better it is at gap-filling. "Thick" stays where you put it!  The "Medium" is great for model construction. The water-thin "Thin" version wicks into tight joints and cracks, dries more quickly and is great for repairs. 

Thin CA can bond skin almost instantly, care should be taken while using it!
Not for use by children, for adult use only.

This glue is NOT foam-safe and should not be use on foam products, I also sell foam safe glue in my other listings.  

All the CA-Plus Adhesives CA glues are triple-distilled for the highest possible quality and are "mil-spec" - originally offered for industrial use, these products are now available for the hobby market. Specifications and MSDS information is available on the CA-Plus web site. RabidModels is the official distributor for CA-Plus adhesives.

FREE SHIPPING..Plantable wildflower seed drops are packed with premium wildflower seeds which sprout and grow when planted. Toss into vacant lots or abandoned areas to add beauty to these urban spaces. They're also great to plant in a garden or pot to grow a beautiful cluster of wildflowers.

Planting instructions for seed drops:
For best results: Find a sunny area. Gently rake the area to loosen the soil then place the seed cap on soil and push down so seed cap is half sunk in the soil. This will provide a good area for roots establish in soil. Water area to keep soil completely moistened during germination (approximately the first 3-7 days) , then water as needed. They can also be planted in a pot indoors.

Guerrilla Gardening Method:
If you see a plot of land that could use a little color with flowers simply toss the seed drops and let nature take care of the rest. However, you can speed it up by activating the seed cap for guerrilla gardening, soak them in a bowl of water until they are squishy...simply find your target and throw!
Happy Gardening...

results.title: STUNNING Art Deco Jewel Toned Dress Clip Hair Combs,PAIR Rhinestone Combs,Fruit Salad,Bridal Hair Comb,Bridal Headpiece,Paste,Gatsby,Flapper
results.description:
A stunning hair comb made using very rare vintage dress clips from the 1920s. These are authentic vintage pieces and not reproductions. The clips are silver pot metal and are leaf shaped. They are totally covered in paste rhinestones. There are portions that are paved with clear stones and the tips of the leaves are covered in jewel toned marquise shaped rhinestones. I love the mix of all the colors, making them rich and unique! Stones are all present and sparkle like crazy- photos aren't doing these justice. Stones have mellowed some with age, as can be expected with 100 year old jewels. 

It is very rare to find these colored dress clips, let alone a pair of them! I have carefully removed the clip backs and secured them to high quality, silver plated hair combs. Each jeweled clip measures 2 3/8" wide by 1 3/4" tall, making them a wonderful size. This is the portion that will be seen when worn in the hair, as the comb will be hidden. Please choose, at checkout, if you prefer a single comb or the pair. Would make an excellent addition to any art deco or vintage themed wedding!

results.description:
*  *  *  WHO WE ARE *  *  *
 
We are a dynamic art company that specializes in the world's leading imagery. Our collection includes original works created by our in-house art team, modern photography, home & office decor trends, antique maps, vintage posters, and everything in between. With an ever growing collection of world-renowned imagery, Lantern Press is a trendsetter known to decorate homes and major resorts - as well as the sets of commercials, films, and television shows.
 
If you're seeking the perfect art to frame for your home or office, we're certain we have a piece you will connect with. Peruse our collection here, featuring thousands of available images in multiple sizes and mediums. We'd also like to take this time to thank you if you've purchased from us before, or plan to today. You are supporting artists who care deeply about their art form, and a company that is proud to print these amazing images in America. Your support allows us to continue doing what we love - creating beautiful art.
 
 
*  *  *  SIZE OPTIONS *  *  *
 
9x12 â High Quality Art Print
 
This size print is great for portfolios, collecting, and a nice gift item.  Many of our customers to a tryptic installation (where you frame 3 and install side by side in a hallway, bedroom, or area that can use more  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes)).  If you are looking for more of a statement piece, we highly recommend moving to a larger size that we offer.   Framing is readily available at any framer and many online frame suppliers.  Printed on a heavy stock on our high-end digital printing press. We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum-quality archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.  We ship this print flat, unless purchased along with another print size listed below.
 
 
12x18 â High Quality Art Print
 
This size print is a statement piece and will be large enough to show detail and capture the attention of the viewer.  Framing is readily available at any framer and many online frame suppliers.  Printed on a heavy stock on our high-end digital printing press.  We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum-quality archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.  We ship this print rolled in a thick mailer tube.
 
 
16x24 â Premium Giclee Print
 
This size print is a crowd favorite!  The size allows you to boast the  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes) in any setting and you gain the value of an ultra high-end giclee at a great price.  Printed on thick (310gsm) textured acid-free watercolor paper. Giclee prints are the standard reproduction medium for museums and premium art galleries worldwide. 
 
Giclee (French for 'to spray') is a printing process where millions of ink droplets are sprayed onto a high-quality paper. This printing process allows for dynamic, almost 3D appearance due to the high color gamut (millions of colors), smooth printing texture, and amazing details in shadows, creating depth.
 
We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum level archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.
 
The Giclee will ship rolled in a thick mailer tube, rolled with archival tissue.
 
 
24x36 â Premium Giclee Print
 
Same as the 16x24 giclee print above, but even bigger!  If you are getting someone an important gift, this is the way to go.  Or, if you are wanting this  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes) to be a statement piece in a room, look no further â this is what you want.  This size is a standard framing size, looks amazing in any setting, and still arrives to you in a convenient tube.
 
*  *  *  IMAGE SIZE / PAPER SIZE *  *  *
 
We print whatâs called âto paperâ which means that we print the image as big as we can onto the paper size.  The 9x12 and 12x18 prints get within about 1/8â to the paper edge, which is great for framing.  The 16x24 and 24x36 are printed âfull bleedâ which means we print the image right to the paper edge, so there is no white border (unless itâs an odd proportion â for instance, if the image is square, and you purchase a 24x36 print, you will receive a 24x24 print).

results.title: Vintage Salisbury Dessert Stand, English Bone China Jewelry Holder, Tiered Server, Tidbit Tray, Tyne Pattern 2069 â Circa 1930âs to 1950âs
results.description:
This lovely tiered vintage English bone china server is from a set that I purchased at an antiques fair on a rainy Sunday in Ireland, while on holiday.  These pieces, in the âTyneâ pattern, #2069, were made sometime between the 1930âs and 1950âs, by the English pottery maker, Salisbury, in Longton, Stoke-on-Trent.  Salisbury features lovely scrolls and florals in cobalt blue, rust, and yellow with gold trim.  There are no chips or cracks that I can find, only fine crazing due to age and use, and perhaps marks made during manufacture. There is some wear to the gold trim but the colors in the pattern are vivid and bright.  Please look at listing photographs and message me with any questions you might have. Considering its age and that it is âpre-lovedâ, it is still a lovely pattern and a beautiful vintage example of the fine potteries from the English, Stoke-on-Trent pottery era. 

This would make a lovely gift for a china collector or anyone who yearns for the beauty of the past. I display it as a jewelry holder to show that it is a versatile tiered stand with many options!

Note:  The jewelry shown in listing photographs is for display only and not included with purchase.

results.title: New Bedford History and Photos in Merchants Bank Centenary Book, 1925
results.description:
This book, titled âThe Centenary of the Merchants National Bankâ, is also the history of the town of New Bedford, Massachusetts.  The book was written by Zephaniah W. Pease, and published in 1925 to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the founding of the Merchants National Bank.  In telling the story of the bank, Mr. Pease also relates the history of New Bedford and its prominence in the whaling industry. 

There are 24 sepia plates, including the leading officers of the bank and views of the bank buildings over the years.  There is a picture of the New Bedford wharf, with a paragraph from âMoby Dickâ below it which refers to New Bedford.  

The book has leather-look hardcover boards, with a paper label bearing the title on the front cover and another on the spine.  The pages are of quality paper with deckle edges.  The book is in very good condition.

The book contains 91 numbered pages, and measures approximately 6-1/2 by 9-1/2 inches. There is no dust jacket.

Thank you for viewing! We appreciate your time!

results.title: Button Converters for Shank Buttons-Silver-Plate Choose 25mm-20mm-15mm Size or Mixed Sizes Pack
results.description:
Glue on Button converters make "bails" for flat back buttons with a shank. 

Also good for affixing a back loop to beads and small objects that can be used in wire work, lacing, and other techniques. These are made with a flat rim and convex interior which "make space" for a shank" up to 1/4" high.

Nice finish-with heavy Silver-plating over a Brass base.. These are "made to last", not flimsy at all, the attached loops (2 loops) are made with wire approximate equivalent to 16 gauge.

I used tons of these when I was making unusual and "found objects" a big boxes of vintage buttons found in the most interesting places into jewelry & affixing "clusters" on bracelets and pendants. The 25mm can be used for 25-6mm buttons (of course) or up to 38mm. The 15mm size can be used (centered) up to 22mm.

You can also use these to create "bails" or cold connectors on the backs of any flat-back Cabochons or undrilled stones or objects. Use them individually or in multiples, fairly lightweight.

Loops can use wire or cord up to 2mm or 3mm (folded).

Choose a size: 25mm or 20mm or 15mm diameter or a Combo sizes pack:

25mm size pack is 8 pieces          15mm size pack is 24pc
20mm size pack is 16 pieces

Combo sizes pack is 30 pieces (4-size 25mm & 10-20mm & 16 pcs of 15mm) The sizes are separated

I also have the 20mm size in Gold-tone finish

Items are NEW, Unused, Old stock (2012)

Button shown as illustrated use-NOT included in this listing

International Buyers:
***Flat Rate International shipping for First or Single item is $5.95 for ALL Countries, add-on extra items in same package for $.75 each. Package shipping is by total weight ($5.72 is base) not number of items. Medium is the most common size and will fit most hands.  All gloves are medium unless specified in the title.  If you consider your hands to be outside of the 'most' category or if you want the gloves to be a loose or a tight fit, choose the gloves designated as 'small' or 'large.' 

Length: 
Measure from where your fingers meet the palm of your hand to the length of the gloves, and that's about where they will come to on your arm/wrist.

Stitch Size: 
All gloves will stretch, fit to most hands because of the ribbing and are made to be close fitting unless noted otherwise in the description above. 

1 is the smallest, most labor intensive size used.  It will also give a more form fitting look and tighter knit. 
10 is the largest size used.  This gives an artistic, handmade, chunky look.

Washing Info:
Hand wash all my knitted goods in cool water with natural soap. Lay flat to dry.

Please Note:
Due to monitor differences, lighting and other factors, actual item colors may be slightly different than how they appear on your screen.

results.title: vintage 1940's WWII era U.S. Navy top coat. Double breasted - Belted waist - Wool Gabardine. Size 38 - 42
results.description:
Clothcraft Clothes - The Joseph & Feiss Co.
'Regulation U.S. Navy Uniform'
wool
Labeled 'Reg 38', but fits larger, up to 42 (please rely on measurements)
mid 1940's

I have had a wide array of military clothing...This is a first.
Black wool Gabardine top coat by The Joseph & Feiss Co. dba Clothcraft Clothes. J & F had military contracts towards the end of World War 2, so this is most likely from 1944-45. Of interest is the bakelite(or early plastic) buttons and buckle, no shiny Gold buttons here, another indication of wartime manufacture.
NOTE: A couple small moth holes on right sleeve, otherwise relatively good condition.

Large 4 1/2" notched lapel, a button hole on either side for full closure leaving top portion of lapel, 3" as a roundabout collar when fastened. A small button underneath each side for a throat latch(missing).
Double breasted. 4 buttons per side. 4/1 closure arrangement.
Shoulder epaulet straps with single button.
Vertical slash pocket each side at hips w/ deep linings.
Cuffs accented with working button strap, 2 pair of tandem buttons each side. 
Detachable belt at waist 2" wide. Black buckle. 2 loops per side.
Single center tail vent, 18" long. 3 button closure.
Half lined in Black satin. Satin tape edge binding.
One vertical access interior breast pocket, right side, Amalgamated Union tag (1939-49) and Clothcraft label inside.
Series of button holes around interior for a removable liner(missing).
Approx. measurements:
23.0" Chest, underarm to under arm
18.5" Shoulder to shoulder
25.5" Sleeve, shoulder to cuff
46.0" Back, bottom of collar to hem
NOTE: Labeled 'Reg 38', coat has a generous fit and without liner can fit up to a 42.

A few more images available. 
Fair to Good condition. As noted a couple small moth holes, right sleeve. Overall press shine. Some wear to edge binding and lining(loose stitching here & there). One pocket has a tear to lining. Missing interior button. This was a trunk find, sold 'as is' Item has not been cleaned by us, and is wrinkled.

results.title: 200+ Lemon Balm Herb Seeds , Under The Sun Seeds
results.description:
Lemon Balm (Melissa Odorata) - Start Lemon Balm seeds and grow the soothing, aromatic herb right on the windowsill! Lemon Balm's most popular use is in soothing herbal teas, where its lemon-scented volatile oils are released. Chopped fresh leaves are also good in salads, soups and stews. The dried leaves are also a perfect ingredient for potpourri and dream pillows. Lemon Balm is also known as Sweet Balm and a synonymous botanical name is Melissa officinalis.
Lemon Balm herb plants will bring the bees and hummingbirds to the garden! They love the fragrant flowers and fragrant heart-shaped leaves. At maturity, the herb plant reaches 12-24 inches tall and 12-18 inches wide. The Lemon Balm leaf can be picked at any time. Larger harvests can be obtained by snipping the upper half of the plant just above a node.
How To Grow Lemon Balm From Herb Seeds: Sow Lemon Balm seeds indoors 6 - 8 weeks before last frost. Use sterile starter mix, and sow the herb seeds on the surface. Do not cover the seeds. Transplant outdoors after frost danger has passed and seedlings have developed their second set of true leaves. For areas with a long growing season, directly sow Lemon Balm herb seeds outside in prepared soil.

For more check us out here!! https://www.etsy.com/shop/UnderTheSunSeeds

results.title: 100+ African Marigold Tall Mix Flower Seeds , Under The Sun Seeds
results.description:
Marigold (Tagetes Erecta Tall Sierra Orange) - This taller variety, known as an African Marigold or Aztec Marigold, looks especially attractive in mass plantings. Sow Marigold seeds to have these large, showy, never fading orange blooms. They will brighten up any garden or flower bed! Tall Marigold flowers are reliable and easily grown from flower seed. The ease of sowing Marigold flower seeds make them popular for children to grow.

Marigold plants will perform well in poor soil with good moisture. African Marigold care involves deadheading spent blooms to promote new flowers. They have a very long bloom season from late spring through fall in most regions. They burst with color all season long! Sow Marigold seeds 6 - 8 weeks before last frost. Use good starter soil and gently press Marigold flower seeds into the soil and lightly cover. When Marigold seedlings are big enough to handle and after acclimatizing the seedlings to outdoor conditions, transplant outdoors after frost danger has passed. Sierra orange Marigold seeds may also be sown directly outdoors after last frost in prepared beds. Marigolds bloom from flower seed in 8 - 10 weeks.

*  *  *  WHO WE ARE *  *  *

You are supporting artists who care deeply about their art form, and a company that is proud to print these amazing images in America. Your support allows us to continue doing what we love - creating beautiful art.
 
 
*  *  *  SIZE OPTIONS *  *  *
 
9x12 â High Quality Art Print
 
This size print is great for portfolios, collecting, and a nice gift item.  Many of our customers to a tryptic installation (where you frame 3 and install side by side in a hallway, bedroom, or area that can use more  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes)).  If you are looking for more of a statement piece, we highly recommend moving to a larger size that we offer.   Framing is readily available at any framer and many online frame suppliers.  Printed on a heavy stock on our high-end digital printing press. We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum-quality archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.  We ship this print flat, unless purchased along with another print size listed below.
 
 
12x18 â High Quality Art Print
 
This size print is a statement piece and will be large enough to show detail and capture the attention of the viewer.  Framing is readily available at any framer and many online frame suppliers.  Printed on a heavy stock on our high-end digital printing press.  We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum-quality archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.  We ship this print rolled in a thick mailer tube.
 
 
16x24 â Premium Giclee Print
 
This size print is a crowd favorite!  The size allows you to boast the  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes) in any setting and you gain the value of an ultra high-end giclee at a great price.  Printed on thick (310gsm) textured acid-free watercolor paper. Giclee prints are the standard reproduction medium for museums and premium art galleries worldwide. 
 
Giclee (French for 'to spray') is a printing process where millions of ink droplets are sprayed onto a high-quality paper. This printing process allows for dynamic, almost 3D appearance due to the high color gamut (millions of colors), smooth printing texture, and amazing details in shadows, creating depth.
 
We use only fine art inks, which are resistant to fading at least 75 years, museum level archival quality, with acid-free pigment to ensure the print doesn't discolor over time.
 
The Giclee will ship rolled in a thick mailer tube, rolled with archival tissue.
 
 
24x36 â Premium Giclee Print
 
Same as the 16x24 giclee print above, but even bigger!  If you are getting someone an important gift, this is the way to go.  Or, if you are wanting this  (Art Prints available in multiple sizes) to be a statement piece in a room, look no further â this is what you want.  This size is a standard framing size, looks amazing in any setting, and still arrives to you in a convenient tube.
 
*  *  *  IMAGE SIZE / PAPER SIZE *  *  *
 
We print whatâs called âto paperâ which means that we print the image as big as we can onto the paper size.  The 9x12 and 12x18 prints get within about 1/8â to the paper edge, which is great for framing.  The 16x24 and 24x36 are printed âfull bleedâ which means we print the image right to the paper edge, so there is no white border (unless itâs an odd proportion â for instance, if the image is square, and you purchase a 24x36 print, you will receive a 24x24 print).

If you have any questions, please contact me, I will respond within 24 hours.

results.title: Two Personalized Flask Sets. FREE US SHIPPING! 30.00 International. Great Groomsman, Wedding, or anytime gift. Listing is for 2 Sets
results.description:
Personalized flasks are a hit! Great for wedding parties and any other special occasion! These come in a nice black presentation box. 
FREE SHIPPING IN THE UNITED STATES AND $30.00 SHIPPING INTERNATIONALLY!

>>> DETAILS <<<
- Listing is for 2 flask sets.
- Each stainless steel flask holds 6 full ounces of your favorite beverage. The four shot glasses are 1oz each. A funnel is also included. Each set comes nicely packaged in a black box with a molded black felt liner. 

>>> PERSONALIZATION "HOW-TO" INFO <<<

1. Include the personalization details you'd like included on each flask. Picture #3 in the listing shows Line Numbers for each line of text on the flasks. 

2. Specify what you want each line to say. There is a section when ordering that you can "Send a note to seller." Or you can just message the details in this thread. 

Also, If the text will be the same on specific lines for every flask (ex. lines 3-8) say exactly that and then only include personalization details for the lines that are different.

EXAMPLE:
Flask 1:
Line 1 - Johnny John's
Line 2 - Best Man Brand

Flask 2:
Line 1 - Joe Schmoe's
Line 2 - Groomsman Brand

etc, etc...


>>> QUALITY, SHIPPING AND OTHER RELEVANT DETAILS <<<
- Each stainless steel flask holds 6 full ounces of your favorite tasty beverage.

- If you don't see quite what you're looking for, please ask! Every design we make is available in some form or another on each of our products.

- Each flask set comes individually packaged in a black presentation box and ships First Class or Priority Mail via USPS.
